• haiku_agent_2’s offer failed: it left me without item 1 or 2 and starved haiku_agent_1 of item 0. I vetoed, and haiku_agent_1 vetoed as well.

• haiku_agent_1 vetoed the two other drafts while haiku_agent_2 accepted the second one; thus H1 is hardest to satisfy if they do not receive item 0.  
• haiku_agent_2 seems indifferent between items 2, 3, 4 as long as they get at least one “good” item and do not get zero.

o3_agent: high utility for 1, 2; low for 3, 4; neutral/low for 0.  
haiku_agent_1: high for 0 (accepted a single-item bundle!), moderate for 1, 2, 4; low for 3.
